e,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Every Few Minutes\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — every 10 min. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Fetch Target Page","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"28f1de1f-72a0-e9aa-36df-de0d79e14e5c","name":"Note: Every Few Minutes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fetch Target Page\n\nGET https://example-market.com/assets — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Extract Listings (CSS) · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"adb8bb0c-7dd6-adae-0a6e-0237aa70bdf6","name":"Note: Fetch Target Page"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Extract Listings (CSS)\n\nExtracts structured values from raw HTML via CSS selectors.\n\nNext: Rows from Arrays","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"b140ac15-8227-9524-b6d1-d3e5f4c42947","name":"Note: Extract Listings (CSS)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Rows from Arrays\n\nCustom JavaScript: Zip parallel arrays into one item per listing\n\nNext: Diff vs Last Run","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"e801c9ad-ffea-2a51-a495-8523ded4e5cc","name":"Note: Rows from Arrays"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Diff vs Last Run · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,1030],"id":"8bce188e-5da2-6fce-7c56-5e0179a0524b","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Diff vs Last Run\n\nDiffs two streams by key into 4 lanes: only-in-A, same, different, only-in-B — the heart of the sync.\n\nPorts: ①→ Alert New Findings · ③→ Update Changed Rows · ④→ Write Fresh Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,520],"id":"fd6f6c45-1020-dc7f-2482-c9738eac4351","name":"Note: Diff vs Last Run"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Alert New Findings\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Diff Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,40],"id":"463c80b9-dfd6-a4ff-ddf8-31f3f9c50adc","name":"Note: Alert New Findings"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Update Changed Rows\n\ngoogleSheets — `appendOrUpdate` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Diff Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,580],"id":"1adb27bc-2e3e-f3ee-d59a-47daa55c315d","name":"Note: Update Changed Rows"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Write Fresh Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Diff Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,1090],"id":"e36636d3-7b0f-5528-179a-06f25612613c","name":"Note: Write Fresh Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Diff Outcomes\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"cf065579-e8ac-2d5d-7fcc-938644979883","name":"Note: Merge Diff Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"774ff7b0-04ce-89df-422c-1fe9defdbcb8","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Load Previous Snapshot 2 · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"0bf722b3-5b25-a568-eb63-11416ab94f58","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot 2\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"fb2c9169-475b-4bfe-3075-6b537d1d196e","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot 2"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"6325cc2e-5832-821f-ff95-fedd63c1e83e","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"8c5c1cb5-74d7-6536-b974-34dc74f44488","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"39f4a2bf-31bc-490e-11b1-2d3e6a18c873","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"e5b3b987-d450-5d52-9ee2-f46249248346","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"a25846b8-0a92-88f5-40cf-f2f6459132c8","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"5f114d62-c75a-3643-376d-e4ea2fd88064","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,1540],"id":"d4fe4e41-08fe-98d4-208b-33ee4f300b8c","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,1540],"id":"fc246e10-7297-5eee-8ea7-a1400c2aa01f","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,1540],"id":"5e74a362-e444-b061-45ff-cbb3c66d6835","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Track market moves with HTTP / REST API and Discord\n\n**Pattern:** Trading Alert · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nTrack market moves with HTTP / REST API and Discord. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual price alerts is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Fetch Target Page → Extract Listings (CSS) → Rows from Arrays → Diff vs Last Run → Alert New Findings → Merge Diff Outcomes → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to trading alert without manual effort\n- Anyone automating price alerts in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"fa8d2402-452d-f841-fc3d-acd211264e1d","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"fa5c58aa-a59c-269d-5a6d-586cd19be97e","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"a443866e-7712-7587-46d2-ae12e0860549","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your price alerts process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"390593aa-cb1e-2d85-a83c-8204b975f9c5","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Every Few Minutes":{"main":[[{"node":"Fetch Target 